cation of valid hydro-testing date on anhydrous ammonia transfer hoses prior to use;



 o Development and/or Modification of Preventive Maintenance Procedures, including:



         o  Increased frequency of internal tank inspection from 10 years to 5 years;

         o  New PM to better identify life cycle of truck unloading Emergency Shutoff Valves;

         o  New PM to test water deluge system located at anhydrous ammonia storage tanks;

         o  Added random ultrasonic thickness scans to existing 3-year PM inspections of ammonia equipment;

         o  Added 100% fluorescent wet magnetic particle examination of longitudinal and circumferential 

            welds during 5-year internal tank inspection PM;

         o  Semi-annual PM to check water content in each anhydrous ammonia storage tank;

         o  Semi-annual PM to exercise dual relief valve isolation valve;

         o  Added tank saddle support area inspections to 5-year internal tank inspection PM;

         o  Added 100% QC check of NPT thread quality prior to installation of threaded components in 

            ammonia service;

         o  Added flange connection inspections with an ammonia vapor monitor to 3-year PM inspections;



 o Addition of a second redundant location for Emergency Shutoff Valve manual actuator for use during anhydrous ammonia truck unloading;



 o Addition of local ammonia leak detection devices (3) at the anhydrous ammonia storage tanks which are continuously monitored by DCS in the control room (complete 1Q-2013);



 o Extension of  anhydrous ammonia tank relief valve discharges above roof line to improve vapor dispersion capability in the event of a relief valve lifting;



 o Addition of a fixed fire water monitor in the vicinity of the anhydrous storage tanks to help emergency response personnel knock down a vapor cloud in the event of a release (complete 1Q-2013);



 o Addition of structural steel roof above the anhydrous ammonia / dilution air blower skid

s to protect them from inclement weather and ice from HRSG roofs;



 o Modification of anhydrous ammonia storage tank piping to eliminate 2"  unions and replaced with ANSI flanges.



         o  Added flange connection inspections with an ammonia vapor monitor to 3-year PM inspections;
